ty of HD 164816 itself by obtaining an orbital\nperiod of 3.82 d, projected masses $m_1 {\\rm sin}^{3} i$ = 2.355(69) M$_\\odot$,\n$m_2 {\\rm sin}^{3} i$ = 2.103(62) M$_\\odot$ apparently seen at low inclination\nangle, determined from high-resolution optical spectra.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 Sep 2012 12:47:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-11"}
